The paper discusses the design and evaluation of interactive machine learning applications, which involves both human-computer interaction and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses algorithmic analysis and computational behavior, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a visual analytics application for guided search suggests a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the discussion of the roles that humans play in interactive machine learning suggests a possible fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
